originalText.text: Walked into the store and there were like 5 sales associates and not a single one thought to say hello to me or even look at me or in my direction. I never understand this type of behavior from people working in high end stores. Do I not look cool enough? Rich enough? After 10 minutes someone decided it was time to ask me what I was looking for. This type of vibe from sales associates is so unbelievably rude and disrespectful.

originalText.text: I had a very poor experience purchasing from this store, specifically around returning unwanted items.  I purchased an item at the end of October and it arrived a week later.  After two weeks I tried to either return or exchange the item but was told that an exchange would be out of policy given the original purchase date.  I said that this was not an item that I wanted and asked for any solutions to the situation but was essentially told to pound sand.  Through persevering, I ultimately exchange the item (for one of greater value) but this experience left me not wishing to purchase from this company again.  By contrast, I had a similar situation at Chanel and they were happy to exchange for an item of equal or higher value.  I can only speculate that it‚Äôs the store‚Äôs poor management leads them to blindly follow policy as opposed to making commercial decisions that generate more earnings and keep future clients.
